<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 2 Spells</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: Where can I find 'Elnerick's Electrical Rendering'?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: Elnerick's is known to still drop from the 'Thought Horror Overfiend' (THO) in 'The Deep.'<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: Where can I find 'Garrison's Superios Sundering'?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: When Luclin was released, there were rumours of it dropping from the THO. Whether or not these are true I cannot confirm, however I can confirm that it no longer drops from him.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: Where can I get Levitation from?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: From the 'Deranged Underbulk' in 'The Deep'. From the zone in, head down the tunnel, take the first right, then take the first left into a dead end. The 'Enraged Underbulk' is a fairly common spawn in this dead end. The camp requires a competent group of mid to high 50s as mobs hit hard in 'The Deep.'<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: Where can I get 'Porlov's Fury' (Dragon's Bane)?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: Quest walkthrough - <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.graffe.com/quests/wrath_spells/porlos_fury/index.htm">www.graffe.com/quests/wra.../index.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> .<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: Where can I get 'Hsagra's Wrath' (Giant's Bane)?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: Quest walkthrough - <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.graffe.com/quests/wrath_spells/hsagras_wrath/index.htm">www.graffe.com/quests/wra.../index.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> .<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: What Dragons can I hit with Dragon's Bane?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: Warders in Sleepers Tomb, Yelinak, Tov dragons with Lord or Lady in their name. No Kunark Dragons.<br>
(Minka Zaubermaus)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: What Giants can I hit with Giant's Bane?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: King Tormax, Vindicator, Velketor, Narandi.<br>
(Minka Zaubermaus)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: Do I need be in melee-range for banes?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: No. Line of Sight is all you need.<br>
(Minka Zaubermaus)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: Is the aggro generated by banes the same as for other direct damage spells?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: No, it is lower than expected considering the damage. *NB* Giant's have very strange aggro so be careful baning them - they don't like it.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: Where can I get 'Concussion' (Brainbite)?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: Quest walkthrough - <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.graffe.com/quests/brain_bite_kunark/index.htm">www.graffe.com/quests/bra.../index.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> .<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: What does 'Concussion' do?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: It removes 400 points of 'aggro' towards you from the monster's hate list.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: How do spell resists work?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: Depending on a monsters resistance to a given 'element', it will have an ability to resist either partially or fully your spells based on their element. The resist levels appear to be quantised such that partial resists always fall as a percentage of maximum damage in the following range {1%, 5%, 10%, 20%, 40%, 60%, 80%}. {1%, 5%, 10%} are much more rare, although the distribution has not been formally analysed.<br>
(Thanks to Armok Komra for analysis)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: Whats the deal with rain spells?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: When used judiciously, rain spells can improve ones damage to mana expended efficiency. The downside is that the rains have a higher chance to be resisted than normal direct damage spell, and since they are area of effect (AoE (*)) you may hit monsters that have been mesmerised and wake them up. The further downside is that a wave of rain cannot kill a monster due to a coding issue so if you cast near the end of a mobs life, it is guaranteed to resist any wave that would kill it. On the plus side, you can cast these and then cast other spells whilst the rains are still descending.<br>
<br>
Discussing whether rains are any good, is generally as productive as arguing religions. For what its worth, when I parsed my usage of them, I found that the added resists and extra time I had to spend moving around to ensure that I wasn't going to hit mesmermised monsters (which could have been spend medding) negated any benefit from these spells. They can help you kill steal more effectively however!<br>
<br>
Addendum: Whizbang Dustyboots, a great advocate of rains claims that he has killed mobs with them. Whilst I've never experienced this, and it directly contradicts a statement by Verant (who claim rains were set to not kill mobs due to an xp allocation issue) I mention this in order to present both sides.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (*) Which is a misgnomer (**), they should be Area of Affect. The 'effect' is the dmg done, the 'affect' is the act of inflicting that damage<br>
<br>
(**) 'Misgnomer' - noun, derived from research showing that everything ill in the world, can be directly traced to the intervention of gnomes.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: What are 'Lures'?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: Spells with attrocious ratios, that whilst less likely to be resisted are seldom used these days as Verant wisely lowered magical resistances across the board. Mages seem to really want them.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: What are 'Ancient' spells?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: These are very high level and rare spells that one should never expect to scribe. They are intended to be the ultimate spells in a wizards repetior and to seperate a Sorceror who lives in 'Velketor's Labyrinth' from one who live in the 'Arx Seru.'<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: Thats a kick in the teeth!</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: Nothing in life worth having is free of cost.<br>
(P.S. 'kick in the teeth' is a banned phrase, I only used it for the amusement of regulars.)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: Some 'uber mobs' seem to resist all my spells although they shouldn't according to my friend, what gives?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: You may well need to be standing in melee range. Verant added this to stop casters exploiting pathing to nuke monsters from outside of their melee range whilst the monster was unable to retaliate.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: Any other nasty tricks they put in to stop monsters being cast at without being able to damage the player?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: Yeah, monsters can summon you too! Level 51 and above monsters pre-Luclin can summon you if you are at the top of the hate list and outside melee range, although only if the monster has had several hundered hp of damage inflicted on it. With the addition of Luclin, lower level monsters get this trick too!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: Could they have been smarter about the above two hacks?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: What like make the monster realise it can't hurt you and run away, or perhaps nuke you back or even pull out a bow? Nah never!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: What is 'Specialisation' ('Specialization')</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: This is an interesting one. Its an example of Verant's description having little resemblance to reality. They claim that you have a percantage chance when you cast for this skill to kick in and save you some of the mana cost. The chance is meant to be governed by you skill in specialisation for that given discipline of specialisation.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: What are the 'Specialisation' skill caps?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: One discipline may be up to skill level 200 dependant on your level, whilst the rest are capped at 50.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: So what really happens with 'Specialisation'?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: You save a percantage of the spell cost on every cast, the amount contingent upon your specialisation skill in that discipline.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: How do you know? Thats not what I heard!</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: Because someone used a packet sniffer to check it out (See ShowEQ).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: How much do I save per cast with a 'Specialistation' at 200?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: 10%.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: And at 50?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: 2.5%. (Can you see a pattern? &lt;grin&gt;)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: What should a wizard choose as his primary specialisation?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: Evocation of course!<br>
<br>
