<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 12. Are you Experienced?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: What dictates how much experience I get from a given monster?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: Two things, the monsters level, and the zone it is in.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: So all monsters of the same level give the same base experience, even dragons?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: Yes &amp; Yes.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: So how does the zone affect this?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: Zones have a multiplier known as the ZEM (Zone Experience Multiplier) that is multiplied with the monsters base xp to yield the final reward amount. Some lesser used or more dangers zones have higher ZEMs.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: So potentially I can make faster xp there?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: Yep, but they have higher ZEMs normally because they are a pain in the arse or hard to get to.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: Can you list the ZEMs?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
