<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: Whats the general pvp tactic for a wizard?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: PvP is pretty hard for wizzies with the general availability of resist gear, regen gear and the damage multiplier (of 0.6). Having said that, here are a few things wizzies do:<br>
<br>
- Use the 'Yonder' line of spells to stay constantly out of other players range. Especially useful against melees. Watch out though as it won't let you go uphill...<br>
- Cast invis if you've managed to hide from the opponent, it makes you drop off their targetting unless they have see invis cast.<br>
- Don't ever be grouped with a player you are dualing. They can use /follow to stay locked to you. Especially deadly against rogues.<br>
- Keep your back to the wall if dualing a rogue!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: What are pumice stones?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: The original and no longer sold by vendor version is an instant click debuff spell that. This was judged unfair, so they replaced them with 'Crystalised Pumice' on the vendors, which has a cast time of 5 seconds. &lt;Is that right cast time?&gt;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: How come people still seem to have the old instant cast variety around?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: Because you can use vendors to recharge them if you have a fully charged one in addition to your empty one. To do this, find an unused vendor with some empty slots (you can tell because when you sell them an item, they will display it). Sell them the empty pumice first, then sell them the charged one. Buy both back. You now have two charged pumice stones. This works on other items too, but practicality is dictated by the buy back price. VI will probably get around to nerfing this at some point, but its been around for nearly 3 years at the time of writing. &lt;Is vendor trick correctly described - I've never done it, but thats how I recall it being explained&gt;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: So how do wizards win at pvp?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
A: Well I don't play on a pvp server, but I've been lead to believe that mostly, they creep up on injured players and nuke em... Frankly if you are up against a warrior with 6k hp, resist gear and a fungal tunic, you are going to run oom before you kill them if you try to be honourable. Alternatively, manaburn can be pretty nice for this too.<br>
